THE Federal Government has declared Tuesday, December 25; Wednesday, December 26 and Tuesday January 1, 2019 as public holidays to mark the Christmas, Boxing Day and New Year celebrations. Minister of Interior Lt-Gen. Abdulrahman Dambazau (retd), who made the declaration on behalf of the Federal Government, enjoined Christians faithful and Nigerians to use the period in praying for Nigeriaâ€™s betterment and growth. He called on the citizens to strengthen their resolve to maintain peace and unity before, during and after the general elections, in the spirit of the season.